column2: calm- hot and muggy- partly sunny day but sunny suring
calm and sunny-lake down about another 1 1/2 in.- beaches appearing
lake closer to normal high water-choppier than usual
little ripples-sunny but hazy- lake down 9 inches

column1: still no waterfowl on the lake

column2: gorgeous day- clear- calm.lake level is still lower

Sunny day.  Helper was Andrew Broshat (Son-in law).  Following rules of not wearing sunglasses- and getting as close to the water as reasonable on the Pontoon.  Also took reading on shady side of boat.
Weather was sunny.  Measurements taken with Andrew Broshat.

Sunny- relatively calm day (light chop).  Has been very warm the last few days.  Sunny- relatively calm day (light chop).  Has been very warm the last few days.  Eagle very active this weekend....dropping down for fish on water.
Very calm day.  No water chop- which seems to make a difference on ease in seeing disk.
Light water chop.  Have seen very warm days this summer.  Many days in high 80?s/90.   Close up view of Eagle when measuring.
Light Chop. Cloudy day on Island Lake
Calm with a slight chop.  Another sunny hot day expected.  Has been very warm (90 degrees) for a number of days this week.  Water temperature is warm.
Warm sunny day after several 90 degree days.  Calm waters
Water choppy- sunny day after a severe thunderstorm in the early morning.
Beautiful sunny morning after another night of thunderstorms.  Two eagles sitting in an island tree.
Cloudy day- light chop.  Loons out and about.
Light rain.  Looks and eagles made this a enjoyable trip
Sunny- calm day.  Found a 28" Walleye floating on top....very interesting to see a walleye of that size on Island Lake...survived since we stocked the lake years ago.
Cool- drizzle. Not excited about taking this test.
Windy- cloudy day on lake.  Made reading difficult
Rain just went thru on a cloudy day
Light chop on water.  Sunny day.
